This document is an "IBM Batch Report" PDF file, dated June 15, 2016, for `Electoral Event ID 19694` in NSW, specifically covering `Vote Collection Point Bangor` (ID 2178) and `Batch Number 12`. It details the processing of 50 ballots (`_001` to `_050`) within this batch. Each ballot undergoes a series of automated and manual checks, including `Quality Assurance`, `Initials Checked`, `Official Mark Checked`, `Unusual Markings Checked`, `Formality Result Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, and various `ATL` (Above-the-Line) and `BTL` (Below-the-Line) preference checks (`Preferences Checked`, `Mismatches`, `Saved Checked`, `Breakdown Checked`, `Formal Checked`).

While most checks indicate "OK" for successful processing, the report highlights instances of "HAS ISSUES". For example, Ballot ID `19694NSWHUGH012421780012_001` shows "HAS ISSUES" for `UnusualMarkings Checked` with the code `['AR1']`, and Ballot ID `19694NSWHUGH012421780012_003` also indicates "HAS ISSUES" for `UnusualMarkings Checked` with the code `['L1 ']`.

This document is directly relevant to Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] for "IBM Outputs" from 2016. It is precisely one of the "IBM Batch Report" PDF files requested, dated within the specified timeframe. It provides concrete examples of the detailed ballot processing insights, batch metadata, electoral event context, and specific ballot-level checks, as well as demonstrating the "HAS ISSUES" entries with associated alphanumeric codes (e.g., `AR1`, `L1`) for anomalies, fully aligning with the description of the yielded documents and the scope of the FOI request.
